<asp:Content ID="Content2" ContentPlaceHolderID="ContentPlaceHolder1" Runat="Server">
    <table align="center" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: medium; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" width="60%">
    <tr>
        <td align="center" height="46">
            <div align="center">
                <b style="font-family: Cambria;">PRODUCT INFORMATION</b></div>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>
<table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" height="77" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: medium; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" width="80%">
    <tr>
        <td height="81">
            <p class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large; font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify;">
                Directional Insight International, Inc. takes a business-oriented approach to the selection and development of employees.&nbsp; We assist organizations in making more informed hiring decisions and developing employees to their maximum potential by offering extensively validated assessment tools.</p>
            <p class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large; font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify;">
                The<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><strong>NSight©</strong><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>is an extensively validated, business-oriented human resources assessment instrument that measures a person&#39;s work-related characteristics and helps identify the right people for specific jobs.&nbsp; By matching people with jobs, the<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><strong>NSight©</strong><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>helps people make the right career choices so that they may find success and satisfaction in their workplace.&nbsp; Through the use of the<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><strong>NSight©</strong>, individuals can avoid working at jobs where they may be potentially uncomfortable, unhappy and prone to failure.</p>
            <p class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large; font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify;">
                Our most popular<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span class="auto-style9" style="font-size: large; font-weight: bold;">NSight©</span><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>package is the</span><span class="auto-style9" style="font-size: large; font-weight: bold;"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>NSight© Aptitude and Personality Questionnaire (NAPQ)</span><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;">.&nbsp; The<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="auto-style9" style="font-size: large; font-weight: bold;">NAPQ<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;">measures three aspects of aptitude (verbal reasoning/comprehension, numerical reasoning and word knowledge), one dimension of achievement (visual perception) and nineteen personality characteristics.&nbsp; The personality characteristics break down into the following 
                six sub-topics: Decision Making/Problem Solving Skills, Drives, Stress, Interpersonal Communications, Leadership, Commitment/Persistence. The investment per individual assessment that entails an 11-page analysis supported by a comprehensive telephone consultation detailing the results of NAPQ in relationship to the position under review is $198.&nbsp; However, quantity pricing that enhances affordability can be viewed by clicking </span><a href="javascript:myopen()"><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;">here</span></a><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;">.</span></p>
            <p class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large; font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify;">
                The<span class="auto-style9" style="font-size: large; font-weight: bold;"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>NSight© Personality Questionnaire (NPQ)</span><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>is for those who wish to assess the 19 job related personality traits only.&nbsp; These nineteen personality characteristics break down into the following six sub-topics: Decision Making/Problem Solving Skills, Drives, Stress, Interpersonal Communications, Leadership, Commitment/Persistence.&nbsp; This service includes a 9-page analysis detailing the results on<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="auto-style9" style="font-size: large; font-weight: bold;">NPQ</span><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;">.&nbsp; The investment per individual assessment is $168.&nbsp; However, preferred pricing on quantity purchases can be viewed by clicking<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><a href="javascript:myopen()"><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;">here</span></a><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;">.</span></p>
            <p class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large; font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify;">
                The<span class="auto-style9" style="font-size: large; font-weight: bold;"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>NSight© Positive Impressions Questionnaire (NPIQ)</span><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>is an untimed assessment presenting 50 multiple-choice questions that measure traits to define the type of impression you make on others.&nbsp; Topics involving Self-Perception, Emotional Identification, Synergy, Communication Style and Reliability are highlighted in a 5-6 page analysis of the results.&nbsp; The investment per individual assessment is $79, however quantity pricing that can be viewed by clicking<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><a href="javascript:myopen()"><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;">here</span></a><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>greatly enhances affordability.</span></p>
            <p class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large; font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify;">
                The chief architect of the<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span class="auto-style9" style="font-size: large; font-weight: bold;">NSight©</span><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>is Dr. Stephen Overcash, Consulting and Clinical Psychologist for Directional Insight International, Inc.&nbsp; Dr. Overcash is a licensed Psychologist, who has maintained a full service private practice in Clinical Psychology as well as serving as a consultant in business for over 25 years.&nbsp; In addition, he is a lecturer, author, and a former Adjunct Professor of Psychology at Penn State University.</span></p>
            <p class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large; font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify;">
                Penny Reynolds is the founder and president of Texas-based<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span class="auto-style9" style="font-size: large; font-weight: bold;">Directional Insight International, Inc.</span><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;">, publisher of the widely used<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span class="auto-style9" style="font-size: large; font-weight: bold;">NSight Aptitude/Personality Assessment</span><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;">.&nbsp; In addition to her expertise in the hiring process, Penny possesses a wealth of personal experience in the sales arena.&nbsp; The evaluation and selection of successful sales personnel is her specialty.&nbsp; For over twenty-five years, she has been actively involved in multiple facets of the assessment industry; including conducting seminars, writing manuals and providing individualized consulting for a variety of businesses.&nbsp; Many corporations benefit from her 
                expertise as she assists them in hiring, promoting, training and retaining a competent work force.&nbsp; Penny participated in the design of the</span><span class="auto-style9" style="font-size: large; font-weight: bold;"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>NSight©</span><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;">.</span></p>
            <p class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large; font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify;">
                Our selection service options are extensive; including the measurement of cognitive resources, personality constructs, customer service know-how, Intelligence Quotient, mechanical abilities, sales &amp; supervisory comprehension, personal interests, attitudes, values and professional integrity.&nbsp; Our development service options include consulting, one-on-one coaching, benchmark studies, retention studies and the design of hiring standards specific to an organization and position.</p>
            <p style="font-size: large; font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify;">
                You may click on <a href="contact_us.aspx" target="_self"><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;">Contact Us</span></a><span class="auto-style8" style="font-size: large;"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>to locate Dr. Stephen Overcash and/or Penny Reynolds.</span><br />
            </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>
